In today’s AI-driven landscape, building applications is no longer limited to writing isolated pieces of code. Modern systems require the integration of user interfaces, backend logic, intelligent models, and data storage. As part of my GenAI Learning Challenge, I built a complete application called AI Notes App that brings all these components together into a single working system.

This project helped me move beyond theoretical understanding and gain practical experience in building a real-world AI-powered application.

## Project Overview

AI Notes App is a web-based application that allows users to interact with an AI model and store the conversation for future reference. Unlike simple AI demos that only generate responses, this application maintains a history of interactions, making it more useful and closer to real-world use cases.

The core idea is to combine AI response generation with persistent data storage and a user-friendly interface.

## System Architecture

The application follows a simple architecture where each component has a clear responsibility.

The user interacts with a web interface, which sends requests to a FastAPI backend. The backend processes the request, communicates with the AI model to generate a response, and stores both the user input and the generated output in a MongoDB database. The stored data is then retrieved and displayed back to the user.

This flow demonstrates how different layers of an application work together in a structured manner.

## Tech Stack

FastAPI is used to build the backend API due to its speed and simplicity. It enables efficient handling of requests and responses.

MongoDB is used as the database to store chat data. Since it is a NoSQL database, it allows flexible storage of documents such as user messages, responses, and timestamps.

The Gemini API is used as the AI model to generate intelligent responses based on user input.

Jinja2 templates are used to create a simple web interface that connects the frontend with the backend.

## How the Application Works

When a user enters a message in the interface, the request is sent to the FastAPI backend. The backend forwards this message to the AI model, which generates a response. This response, along with the original message and a timestamp, is stored in MongoDB. The stored data is then displayed back in the interface, allowing users to view their conversation history.

This continuous cycle of input, processing, storage, and display forms the core functionality of the application.

## Features

The application provides a simple and interactive interface for users to communicate with the AI model. It stores all conversations in a database, allowing users to revisit previous interactions. It also includes a feature to clear stored notes, giving users control over their data.

Additionally, the application follows best practices by using environment variables to manage sensitive information such as API keys and database connection strings.

## Example Interaction

A user can enter a message such as “Hello” and receive a response from the AI model. Similarly, asking a question like “What is Artificial Intelligence?” will return a meaningful explanation generated by the model. All such interactions are stored and displayed in the application.

## Key Learnings

This project provided hands-on experience in building APIs using FastAPI, integrating AI models using API keys, and managing data using MongoDB. It also helped in understanding how frontend and backend systems communicate with each other.

Another important learning was the use of environment variables to securely manage sensitive data, which is a critical practice in real-world applications.

## Challenges Faced

One of the main challenges was integrating multiple components into a single workflow. Ensuring smooth communication between the API, AI model, and database required careful structuring. Handling real-time responses and storing data efficiently were also important aspects of the development process.

Overcoming these challenges improved my understanding of full-stack development and system design.

## Conclusion

The AI Notes App represents a complete application that combines user interaction, backend processing, AI integration, and data persistence. It demonstrates how modern AI systems are built by connecting different technologies into a unified solution.

This project has strengthened my confidence in building practical AI applications and has laid a strong foundation for exploring more advanced systems in the future.

